<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-415-584  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 415 584.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Software Engineering  July 1989 v15 n7p875(15).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Reasoning about time in higher-level language software.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shaw, Alan C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A methodology is developed for analyzing and proving assertionsabout time and specifying timing properties in concurrent,higher-level language programs and program elements.andP;  Higher-levellanguages are being used more often to create concurrent,real-time software applications.andP;  Such languages do not,typically, include the capability to predict the timing behaviorof such programs, nor reason about time within the programs.andP;  Thenew methodology is based on the extrication of upper and lowerbounds of program element execution times and the extension ofHoare logic to include the effects of updating in real-timeapplications.andP;  Structured timing schemas, timing bounds, andassertions are developed for a variety of programs and statementtypes.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Research and DevelopmentReal-Time SystemsTime-Driven SystemsProgramming LanguagesNew TechniqueSystems Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>